claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: A flowchart (CONSORT diagram) showing subject disposition: 4648 subjects enrolled and randomized into two groups: FluBlok (n=2344) and Placebo (n=2304). Each arm details discontinuations (with reasons) and the resulting safety populations. The figure presents participant enrollment and disposition data and does not mention production methods, recombinant HA expression, insect cells, or BEVS. It does not support the claim.
